  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 23-year-old woman comes to the physician for evaluation of two masses on her right auricle for several months. The masses appeared a few weeks after she had her ear pierced and have increased in size since then. A photograph of her right ear is shown. Which of the following is the most likely cause of these findings?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Implantation of epidermis into the dermis"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Proliferation of mature adipocytes"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Increased production of disorganized extracellular matrix"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Malignant transformation of keratinocytes"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Excess deposition of collagen in parallel"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Implantation of the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"exaxv5\">epidermis</a></span> into the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"Qxauw5\">dermis</a></span> is the pathomechanism underlying <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eu08G3&anker=Z8a411025f66661e44d5bd17d7a0781fb\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eu08G3\" data-anker=\"Z8a411025f66661e44d5bd17d7a0781fb\" data-section-id=\"vcdAVK0\" data-sememe-id=\"DTY1Go\">epidermoid cyst</a></span> formation. <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eu08G3&anker=Z8a411025f66661e44d5bd17d7a0781fb\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eu08G3\" data-anker=\"Z8a411025f66661e44d5bd17d7a0781fb\" data-section-id=\"vcdAVK0\" data-sememe-id=\"DTY1Go\">Epidermoid cysts</a></span> are slow-growing, firm, painless <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a> and can be preceded by trauma to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a>. Unlike the lesions seen in this patient, they are usually not <span data-sememe-id=\"U6Xb4_\">hyperpigmented</span>. Implantation of the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"exaxv5\">epidermis</a></span> into the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"Qxauw5\">dermis</a></span> is not associated with <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid</a></span> formation.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_58a6d14298b10.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>A small, solitary, flesh-colored, round, nodular lesion with a small central pore.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Z2a4436e6b50383d2f3a205f11f9c829a\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Z2a4436e6b50383d2f3a205f11f9c829a\" data-section-id=\"aFXQg-\">proliferation</a> of mature <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=k60mOS&anker=Zc75d9d9aa2bfe16ff4ca152a47d77869\" data-learningcard-id=\"k60mOS\" data-anker=\"Zc75d9d9aa2bfe16ff4ca152a47d77869\" data-section-id=\"5FciiV0\" data-sememe-id=\"SQXyvB\">adipocytes</a></span> is the mechanism underlying <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eu08G3&anker=Za534a386220e09d722be0a49058e4565\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eu08G3\" data-anker=\"Za534a386220e09d722be0a49058e4565\" data-section-id=\"8cdOVK0\" data-sememe-id=\"iBaJ0M\">lipoma</a> </span>formation, which can occur in almost any part of the body (e.g., head, neck, chest, and back). Unlike the lesions seen in this patient, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eu08G3&anker=Za534a386220e09d722be0a49058e4565\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eu08G3\" data-anker=\"Za534a386220e09d722be0a49058e4565\" data-section-id=\"8cdOVK0\" data-sememe-id=\"iBaJ0M\">lipomas</a> are usually <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a>-colored and rarely located in/around the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">ears</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Z2a4436e6b50383d2f3a205f11f9c829a\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Z2a4436e6b50383d2f3a205f11f9c829a\" data-section-id=\"aFXQg-\">proliferation</a> of <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=k60mOS&anker=Zc75d9d9aa2bfe16ff4ca152a47d77869\" data-learningcard-id=\"k60mOS\" data-anker=\"Zc75d9d9aa2bfe16ff4ca152a47d77869\" data-section-id=\"5FciiV0\" data-sememe-id=\"SQXyvB\">adipocytes</a></span> is not associated with trauma and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid</a> formation.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5a9aa1a50f2de.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Several large, ovoid, lobulated nodules are visible on the flexor surface of the forearm.</p><p>The size, shape, location, and distribution of the lesions are consistent with lipomas.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">Keloids</a> are formed from the <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>hyperproliferation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Za4a8b0444de65a37fb689ea9c7ee3b47\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Za4a8b0444de65a37fb689ea9c7ee3b47\" data-section-id=\"MocMcW0\" data-sememe-id=\"9GbNYv\">fibroblasts</a></b></span>, which results in <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>disorganized</b></span> overproduction of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Z801cd09cf81a55078c80eceef3d71d36\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Z801cd09cf81a55078c80eceef3d71d36\" data-section-id=\"noc7cW0\">collagen types</a> I and III</b></span>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">Keloids</a> are most commonly seen in dark-skinned individuals. Common locations for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> include the earlobes, face (e.g., cheeks), upper extremities, chest, and neck. See “<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z3b974deba346a7cef7f635b761d9a9b5\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z3b974deba346a7cef7f635b761d9a9b5\" data-section-id=\"BsWzC50\">Clinical features of hypertrophic scars and keloids</a>” table.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Malignant transformation of <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z43521d292af098a1f51dbc362638bb31\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z43521d292af098a1f51dbc362638bb31\" data-section-id=\"otc0eV0\" data-sememe-id=\"fVXkFC\">keratinocytes</a></span> is the pathomechanism underlying <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ik0Y6T&anker=Z22a615a6799c9d36261ff95cf268624a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ik0Y6T\" data-anker=\"Z22a615a6799c9d36261ff95cf268624a\" data-sememe-id=\"dM0ong\">cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma</a></span> (c<span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">SCC</a></span>) formation. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ik0Y6T&anker=Z22a615a6799c9d36261ff95cf268624a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ik0Y6T\" data-anker=\"Z22a615a6799c9d36261ff95cf268624a\" data-sememe-id=\"dM0ong\">SCC of the skin</a> typically develops in sun-exposed areas, such as the face and neck. Unlike the lesions seen in this patient, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ik0Y6T&anker=Z22a615a6799c9d36261ff95cf268624a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ik0Y6T\" data-anker=\"Z22a615a6799c9d36261ff95cf268624a\" data-sememe-id=\"dM0ong\">cSCC</a> usually appear <span data-sememe-id=\"0wYehr\">plaque</span>-like, nodular, <span data-sememe-id=\"jeX_AC\">verrucous</span>, or ulcerative, and are most commonly seen in elderly men. Malignant transformation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z43521d292af098a1f51dbc362638bb31\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z43521d292af098a1f51dbc362638bb31\" data-section-id=\"otc0eV0\" data-sememe-id=\"fVXkFC\">keratinocytes</a> is not associated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid</a> formation.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5489b8294c632.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>A single, asymmetric cutaneous lesion with an irregular border and varied pigmentation can be seen.</p><p>Histologic examination revealed squamous cell carcinoma in situ.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"uBapcM\">Hypertrophic scars</a> are caused by the excess formation and parallel deposition of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Ze161de87087c9facb087f3c79d5fd9db\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Ze161de87087c9facb087f3c79d5fd9db\" data-section-id=\"noc7cW0\" data-sememe-id=\"AKbRQu\">type III collagen</a>. Unlike the lesion seen in this patient, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"uBapcM\">hypertrophic scars</a> usually protrude above the surface of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> but are confined within the original wound margins. Although <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid</a> formation is also caused by the excess formation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Zf300f7a0c31e992a872dd5061a567b0e\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Zf300f7a0c31e992a872dd5061a567b0e\" data-section-id=\"noc7cW0\" data-sememe-id=\"yGbdbv\">collagen</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Z2ffc5ce57d97d4b2fc17b6088691c31a\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Z2ffc5ce57d97d4b2fc17b6088691c31a\" data-section-id=\"noc7cW0\">collagen fibers</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid scars</a> are typically disorganized.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_59a8462c2ffaa.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>A linear, erythematous raised scar is visible in the center of the image.</p><p>These features are characteristic of a hypertrophic scar, which results from abnormal wound repair (i.e., overgrowth of fibroblastic tissues during skin healing).</p></div></div></div>",
      "hint": "This patient's history of trauma, followed by tissue growth beyond the boundaries of the original lesion is suggestive of keloid formation. The brownish-red color of the lesion shown supports this diagnosis.",
