      "text": "Patient Information\nAge: 29 years\nGender: F, self-identified\nRace/Ethnicity: unspecified\nSite of Care: clinic\nHistory\nReason for Visit/Chief Concern: “I pierced my ear and now have these lumps on that ear.”\nHistory of Present Illness:\n\n\npierced the right ear 6 months ago\n\n\n2 lumps appeared at the site of injury a few weeks after the piercing and have been growing\n\nmoderate discomfort and pruritus on the right ear\npatient is concerned that it might be an infection or cancer\n\nPast Medical History:\n\ngeneralized anxiety disorder\ngastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)\n\nMedications:\n\nescitalopram\nomeprazole\n\nAllergies:\nno known drug allergies\nFamily History:\n\nsister: rheumatoid arthritis\nmother: deceased at age 55 years from breast cancer\nfather: hypertension, hyperlipidemia\n\nPsychosocial History:\n\ndoes not smoke cigarettes\ndrinks six alcoholic beverages weekly\ndoes not use unprescribed drugs or other substances\nsexually active with one male partner\n\nPhysical Examination\n\n\nTemp\nPulse\nResp\nBP\nO2 Sat\nHt\nWt\nBMI\n\n\n36.0°C (96.8°F)\n65/min\n16/min\n121/83 mm Hg\n-\n170 cm(5 ft 7 in)\n63 kg(139 lb)\n21.8 kg/m2\n\n\n\n\nAppearance: awake and alert; not in acute distress\nSkin: a photograph is shown\n\nNeck: no jugular venous distention\nPulmonary: clear lung fields bilaterally\nCardiac: regular rhythm; no murmurs\nAbdominal: soft, nontender; nondistended\nNeurologic: fully oriented; no abnormalities\n\n\nWhich of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
