      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Reassurance and <span data-sememe-id=\"2ycTeU0\">watchful waiting</span> are not appropriate for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> because the lesions do not spontaneously regress. This strategy is more appropriate for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"uBapcM\">hypertrophic scars</a> because they typically regress spontaneously.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Diagnosis of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> is usually clinical, based on typical lesion appearance and history of trauma or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a> to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">the ear</a> (e.g., piercing). Because <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dP0odT&anker=Z2fe1c78bc3078f0625f8db0f39b93107\" data-learningcard-id=\"dP0odT\" data-anker=\"Z2fe1c78bc3078f0625f8db0f39b93107\" data-section-id=\"-tXDT-\" data-sememe-id=\"VBbG-D\">skin biopsy</a> can promote hyperproliferative scarring, this procedure should be avoided unless <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"OHXIqz\">malignancy</a> is suspected.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Intralesional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">corticosteroid</a> injections</b></span> are indicated <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid scars</a> that persist or continue to grow &gt; 4 weeks after injury</b></span>. In addition, all patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> should receive one or more noninvasive treatments (e.g., moisturizers, silicone creams, pressure therapy). If <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> persist or continue to grow &gt; 6 months, the patient should be referred to a specialist, who will consider additional therapies and/or surgical excision. Prevention measures for developing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> include adequate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Zf8cec21d4434239c656121b578f781b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Zf8cec21d4434239c656121b578f781b8\">wound care</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-section-id=\"ZvXZA-\">scar</a> moisturizing, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jF0_33&anker=Zeb8cd22d4e5518c82d547defb1386c12\" data-learningcard-id=\"jF0_33\" data-anker=\"Zeb8cd22d4e5518c82d547defb1386c12\" data-section-id=\"MsWMv50\" data-sememe-id=\"S71yOR0\">photoprotective measures</a>, and in cases of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a>, making <span data-sememe-id=\"DT01G2\">incisions</span> parallel to relaxed <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> tension lines.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"VfbGOG\">Cryotherapy</span> is an adjunctive treatment for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> that can be considered if first-line treatment fails.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Surgical excision is indicated for patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hQ0cDf&anker=Zd2a2f37a9ccc074254e9331a5ba6126c\" data-learningcard-id=\"hQ0cDf\" data-anker=\"Zd2a2f37a9ccc074254e9331a5ba6126c\" data-section-id=\"u4cpOc0\" data-sememe-id=\"0Q0euf\">contractures</a> due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> and can also be considered for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> that persist &gt; 12 months after all other therapies have been utilized. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">Surgery</a> is not a first-line therapy for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> as recurrence is common following excision. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">Surgery</a> is more appropriate for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"uBapcM\">hypertrophic scars</a> because recurrence is infrequent.</div>",
      "hint": "This patient's well-defined, round, red, smooth lesions that extend beyond the boundaries of the injury are consistent with keloids. They most commonly occur on the earlobes (e.g., due to piercing), face, and upper extremities.",
