    {
      "text": "A 22-year-old African American man presents for follow-up 2 weeks after an excisional biopsy of a suspicious nevus on his sternum. The sutures have been removed, and the wound has healed well by primary intention. He has a personal history of developing a large, firm scar on his earlobe after a piercing five years ago and expresses significant concern about developing a similar scar on his chest. Examination of the surgical site reveals a well-approximated, linear, non-erythematous scar. The earlobe has a 1.5 cm firm, rubbery nodule. Which of the following is the most effective intervention at this stage to minimize the risk of keloid formation at the surgical site?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Topical application of onion extract cream"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Daily massage with topical vitamin E oil"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Referral for localized radiation therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Administration of intralesional triamcinolone"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Application of silicone gel sheeting"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>While commonly marketed for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-section-id=\"ZvXZA-\">scar</a> improvement, there is a lack of high-quality evidence to support the <span data-sememe-id=\"NfW-mk0\">efficacy</span> of topical onion extract in preventing or treating <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z10ae98ee4651a3fb189b8b7994fa651c\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"uBapcM\">hypertrophic scars</a>. Multiple studies have shown it to be no more effective than simple emollients or placebo. Therefore, it is not recommended as a first-line, evidence-based intervention.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Although <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-section-id=\"ZvXZA-\">scar</a> massage is often recommended to improve pliability, evidence that it prevents <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid</a> formation is lacking. Furthermore, studies on topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ao0ReS&anker=Za9ba553828f4a0900f6d53a825651453\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ao0ReS\" data-anker=\"Za9ba553828f4a0900f6d53a825651453\" data-section-id=\"Qpcu6W0\" data-sememe-id=\"JgbswG\">vitamin E</a> have not shown a benefit over placebo in improving <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-section-id=\"ZvXZA-\">scar</a> appearance and, in some individuals, can cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xs09th&anker=Z641368c7d5f61c4e977723a721353fef\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xs09th\" data-anker=\"Z641368c7d5f61c4e977723a721353fef\" data-sememe-id=\"x2XEPx\">allergic contact dermatitis</a>. This approach is not considered an effective <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Wj0Pzf&anker=Z36cbb165fdbe3a26b21fa941d90737fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"Wj0Pzf\" data-anker=\"Z36cbb165fdbe3a26b21fa941d90737fe\" data-section-id=\"fGXkAz\" data-sememe-id=\"cGaayN\">primary prevention</a> strategy for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=L50wkg&anker=Zd120147b0e92bb22668d9e60dfbdc88b\" data-learningcard-id=\"L50wkg\" data-anker=\"Zd120147b0e92bb22668d9e60dfbdc88b\" data-sememe-id=\"-L0DZS\">Radiation therapy</a> is an effective <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TH06ph&anker=Zbe736188466767a56a07774a11dee306\" data-learningcard-id=\"TH06ph\" data-anker=\"Zbe736188466767a56a07774a11dee306\" data-section-id=\"l1WvS40\" data-sememe-id=\"3TYSqo\">adjuvant treatment</a> used to prevent the recurrence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a>, but it is typically administered within 24-48 hours immediately following the surgical excision of an existing, recalcitrant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid</a>. It is not used as a primary preventative measure for a simple <span data-sememe-id=\"sebtZG\">biopsy</span> site due to the potential long-term risks, including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> changes and secondary <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"OHXIqz\">malignancy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Intralesional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">corticosteroids</a> are a first-line treatment for existing, active <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloids</a>, not a primary prophylactic measure for a newly healed, flat <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-section-id=\"ZvXZA-\">scar</a>. This intervention is appropriate when a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z599c50b1cc4bdb1ffd8e64279c5da622\" data-section-id=\"wsWhC50\" data-sememe-id=\"RBal0M\">keloid</a> has already formed and is causing symptoms like <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hL0cxg&anker=Zab8bccb1884a614e892b07510e605271\" data-learningcard-id=\"hL0cxg\" data-anker=\"Zab8bccb1884a614e892b07510e605271\" data-sememe-id=\"xg0Ex2\">pruritus</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>, or is actively growing. Using it prophylactically on a well-healed primary <span data-sememe-id=\"DT01G2\">incision</span> is not standard practice.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Silicone gel sheeting</b></span> is a widely accepted, non-invasive <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>first-line therapy</b></span> for the prevention of both <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-t0DT3&anker=Z593e7d4f649b23852d9063b067eb909a\" data-learningcard-id=\"-t0DT3\" data-anker=\"Z593e7d4f649b23852d9063b067eb909a\">hypertrophic scars and keloids</a></b></span>. It should be initiated as soon as the wound has fully epithelialized, typically 1-2 weeks after <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a>. The mechanism is thought to involve increasing hydration of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zc001b39d3b1b6e0a8e0774fab9aea2cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zc001b39d3b1b6e0a8e0774fab9aea2cf\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"UxabD5\">stratum corneum</a> and creating an occlusive barrier, which helps regulate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Za4a8b0444de65a37fb689ea9c7ee3b47\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Za4a8b0444de65a37fb689ea9c7ee3b47\" data-section-id=\"MocMcW0\" data-sememe-id=\"9GbNYv\">fibroblast</a> production and reduce <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Zf300f7a0c31e992a872dd5061a567b0e\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Zf300f7a0c31e992a872dd5061a567b0e\" data-section-id=\"noc7cW0\" data-sememe-id=\"yGbdbv\">collagen</a> deposition. It is safe, effective, and should be worn for at least 12 hours per day for several months.</div>",
      "hint": "For high-risk patients, such as this individual with a personal history of keloids and an incision in a high-tension area like the sternum, prophylaxis is key.",
